tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE bioengineered_food_products (
    product_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    product_name TEXT,
    category TEXT,
    price DECIMAL,
    popularity_score FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE bioengineered_foods (
  food_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  food_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  category VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  price DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,
  description TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE market_analysis (
  analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  food_id INT,
  analysis_date DATE,
  demand INT,
  preference VARCHAR(50),
  FOREIGN KEY (food_id) REFERENCES bioengineered_foods(food_id)
);

CREATE TABLE bioengineered_products (
	product_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
	product_name VARCHAR(255),
	price DECIMAL,
	production_date DATE,
	expiry_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE FoodProducts (
   id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   product_name VARCHAR(50),
   category VARCHAR(50),
   price DECIMAL(10, 2),
   production_date DATE,
   expiration_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE MarketTrends (
   id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   product_id INT,
   trend_date DATE,
   demand_rating INT,
   popularity_rating INT
);

CREATE TABLE CustomerPreferences (
   id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   customer_id INT,
   product_id INT,
   preference_score INT,
   rating_rating INT
);
